snippet: Twenty-five years after the debut of “Seinfeld,” the Brooklyn Cyclones baseball team celebrated the iconic comedy with a theme night.
abstract: Brooklyn Cyclones baseball team and fans celebrate debut of Seinfeld television program 25 years ago; communal effort to send up a show built on the minutia of observational humor keeps most of the 8,241-person sellout crowd around for Cyclones' worst game of season.
lead_paragraph: Twenty-five years after the debut of “Seinfeld,” the Brooklyn Cyclones baseball team celebrated the iconic comedy with a theme night.

headline.seo: Brooklyn Cyclones’ ‘Seinfeld’ Night Pays Tribute to a Show About Nothing
headline.main: Festivus Poles. Close-Talker Mascot. Yada, Yada, Yada.
